text: During our American Politics panel in Palm Beach yesterday I quoted Chris Matthews in framing a question to my pal Jeff Greene: In the book 'Tip and the Gipper, When Politics Worked,' the author quotes President Reagan,

"Tip if I had a ticket to heaven and you didnt have one, too, I would give mine away and go to hell with you." The cooperative tone at High Ridge on Sunday, in marked contrast to the animus that exists in Washington, D.C., shows that some how and some way a more collaborative

and constructive dialogue is possible and that our deeply partisan and broken political system can still be fixed. On this somber day its important to remember the possibilities that remain in front of us... piped.video/watch?v=I47Y6VHc… @tomkeene @jimcramer @TeamCavuto
